Pre-Game Insights: Jordan Wicks has shown poise beyond his years and should play well against a Dodgers lineup that can be susceptible to left-handed pitching.
Bobby Miller has struggled recently, allowing 7 earned runs in his last outing but has shown the ability to bounce back quickly.
The Cubs' bats have been hot lately, led by Cody Bellinger's resurgence and Seiya Suzuki's power surge.
The Dodgers have been nearly unbeatable at Dodger Stadium this season, and their home field advantage should give Miller a significant boost in confidence and performance.
